  <div id="poddiscbox" class="poddisc1">
    <h3>The Black Tapes is a fictional supernatural investigation podcast; the main character, journalist Alex Regan teams up with scholar and skeptic Dr. Richard Strand to investigate his 'black tapes,' a series of supposedly unsolved paranormal happenings. This podcast has amazing sound design and attention to detail, although the acting can be stiff on occasion. The series sadly has an aborted ending due to conflict between the creators, but there are still two amazing seasons.</H3><h3> Production Status: Completed/Indefinite Hiatus.</h3><h3> 
      Personal Status: Completed.</h3>
  </div>
  <div id="poddiscbox2" class="poddisc2">
    <h3>A podcast titan, The Magnus Archives has set the bar for supernatural horror since its premiere in 2016. This podcast follows Jonathan Sims, recently-hired archivist for the lofty Magnus Institute. What he thinks is a disorganized mess left behind by his doddering predecessor slowly evolves into a cacophony of madness and horror; although highly anthological in the beginning, patterns behind to forms and names will start to become familiar rather quickly. The show has very good audio design, although the focus is primarily on a single character reading and thus your enjoyment is entirely based on if you enjoy his performance. A massive project, the Magnus Archives spans 200 episodes and approximately 85 hours of content.</h3><h3>Production Status: Completed.</h3><h3>Personal Status: Completed</h3>
  </div>
  <div id="poddiscbox3" class="poddisc3">
    <h3>The story of Olive Hill is murky and enigmatic. What is billed as a true-crime investigation quickly runs into problems reconciling itself with the numerous paranormal answers for the central question: How did two girls, across town from one another, disappear on the same night at the same time, never to be seen again? The acting of Olive Hill can be somewhat stilted at times, but never enough to be an obvious distraction. In terms of story, the narrative and dialogue are well-crafted, making meaningful connections and allusions throughout. One season.</h3><h3>Production Status: Completed.</h3><h3>Personal Status: Completed.</h3>
  </div>
